A police officer has been arrested on the accusation of killing his civilian companion on Tuesday evening.
Via Twitter, the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) identified the murder suspect as Edgar Mokamba, a police constable based at the Nyari patrol base in Gigiri.
“With an AK47 rifle, the officer had been deployed as a station guard moments before he was joined by his regular friend, who frequents the patrol base in Nairobi's Westlands area,” the DCI said.



